he tensions obtaining between perception and the construction of possibility. Concrete text analysis and a determination of the effects intended by the author and the methods he employed as a 'social writer' present Forster in a new light.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aForster, Georg. 4aHalle ‹Saale, 1994›. 4aKongress. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aEwert, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarber, Jörn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarber, Jörn, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHochadel, Oliver, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKronauer, Ulrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeitsch, Helmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPickerodt, Gerhart, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRibeiro Sanches, Manuela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmitter, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUhlig, Ludwig, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348481012940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311093205840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110932058423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110932058/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014